        </div>
        <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
          <div class="keyword">monsterinfo</div>
        </div>
        <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersE-F58"/>
        <p>Though <a href="ch65s07.html#MonstersE-F57">ettins</a> aren't very intelligent, they are cunning fighters.</p>
        <p>They prefer to ambush their victims rather than charge into a straight fight, but once the battle has started, an <a href="ch65s07.html#MonstersE-F57">ettin</a> usually fights furiously until all enemies are dead.</p>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id1753505"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersE-F59"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Superior Two-Weapon Fighting (Ex):</strong></span> An <a href="ch65s07.html#MonstersE-F57">ettin</a> fights with a morningstar or javelin in each hand. Because each of its two heads controls an arm, the <a href="ch65s07.html#MonstersE-F57">ettin</a> does not take a penalty on attack or damage rolls for attacking with two weapons.</p>
          <p>Skills: An <a href="ch65s07.html#MonstersE-F57">ettin's</a> two heads give it a +2 racial bonus on <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills204">Listen</a>, <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills294">Spot</a>, and <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills253">Search</a> checks.</p>
